comment_data.body: I find this issue very confusing. The error is not what I thought it would be. I am trying to narrow it down, but what is happening is that it refuses to compile the `test45.pyx` even when it is empty. I tried pasting some of the other tests into it, and the compilation still silently aborts.
I figured it out. The problem was that the directory was named `test45 - Save The Princess` rather than `test45` like I had expected. Might want to tell the user when he passes in an invalid path.

title: [BUG] Cython silently fails on when trying to compile the following file
